# Dev-only live recorder (needs a human + asciinema; not part of build/CI).
# The committed demo (scripts/demo-flow.sh + scripts/make-cast.mjs) and its
# generated docs/quickstart.cast are versioned so the README can link them.
scripts/record-quickstart.sh

# Dogfood: mnema runs against itself here, so this .mnema/ is a development
# workbench, not a reference project. Its audit chain is knowingly broken and
# truncated by the churn of building the tool (merges, rebases, rewinds), so
# nothing under it — not even the public verification material — is meant to
# be trusted or held up as an example. We therefore ignore .mnema/ WHOLESALE.
#
# This is a deliberate exception for the tool's OWN repo. Adopter projects do
# the opposite (and `mnema init` scaffolds it): commit the markdown mirrors +
# audit chain + public keys, ignore only the rebuildable .mnema/state/ cache.
# The faithful examples of the audit/attestation flow are those adopter repos,
# never this one. (Consequence: with no committed keys/project.hmac-id, the
# wholesale-downgrade defence is inert HERE — accepted, since this chain is a
# throwaway workbench, not something a clone should verify.)
.mnema/

AGENTS.md
docs-local/
